4.19.25  1:24 pm   why is "zh" a sound. I cant think of any words that use the zh sound, only shield. like you don't say "zhield" or "zhack"

      we don't usually spell it like that in english, but we do sometimes have the sound, especially when borrowing from french (french doesnt spell it that way either, it would be usually j or g). the idea is to have a voiced version of "sh", just like "z" is a voiced version of "s". You hear the sound in "genre", "beige", "illusion", "mirage",
